770: \section{CKM Matrix}
771: \label{sec:ckm}
772: 
773: The Cabibbo–Kobayashi–Maskawa (CKM) matrix describes the mixing between different quark flavors in weak interactions. In the Standard Model, its four parameters (three angles and one CP‑violating phase) are free and must be taken from experiment. In Metatime theory, these parameters are not free; they arise from the differences in Berry phases $\gamma_i$ associated with the topological cycles of the quarks on the Kähler manifold.

774: 
